name: Project for Erasmus internship: Spinlet mechanism for water sensor positioning
description: This prototype consists in a spinlet motor that makes the function of moving the sensor up and down, and measuring the water quality in different positions. For this project, we made use of an Arduino protoboard to communicate with the spinlet and configure the moving function. We have also used Raspberry to communicate itself to the Arduino protoboard with Python and making the serial communication from there thanks to it.

name: E-Commerce Project
description: This idea was made for my degree's final project. I've made a online shop where you can do the following actions like: login and register (important in case you want to unlock the shopping cart, the option of booking a ticket for a event, etc.), edit your user data (only the administrator can administrate the products), add and quit products in the cart, and simulate the checkout via PayPal Sandbox. This was deployed in a LAMP server and modified in VS Code via SSH with the 'Remote - SSH' extension.
